    "# Phase 6: Modeling - Forecasting Exploration\n",
    "\n",
    "## Overview\n",
    "\n",
    "Build and evaluate time-series forecasting models to predict future crime trends.\n",
    "\n",
    "### Objectives\n",
    "1. Prepare time-series data\n",
    "2. Test stationarity\n",
    "3. Explore SARIMA and Prophet models\n",
    "4. Evaluate model performance\n",
    "5. Generate forecast predictions\n",
    "\n",
    "### Note\n",
    "This is a starter notebook for forecasting exploration. Expand based on specific business requirements."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": {"cell_type": \"markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Cell 1: Setup and Imports"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": {"cell_type": \"code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import sys\n",
    "from pathlib import Path\n",
    "import pandas as pd\n",
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "import seaborn as sns\n",
    "\n",
    "PROJECT_ROOT = Path.cwd().parent.parent\n",
    "sys.path.insert(0, str(PROJECT_ROOT))\n",
    "\n",
    "from src.data import loader\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"Imports successful\")\n",
    "print(\"Note: Install statsmodels and prophet for full functionality\")\n",
    "print(\"  pip install statsmodels prophet\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": {"cell_type": \"markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Cell 2: Load and Prepare Data"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": {"cell_type": \"code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "df = loader.load_crime_data()\n",
    "\n",
    "if 'date' in df.columns:\n",
    "    df['date'] = pd.to_datetime(df['date'])\n",
    "    \n",
    "    # Create daily time series\n",
    "    ts_data = df.groupby('date').size().reset_index(name='incidents')\n",
    "    ts_data = ts_data.set_index('date')\n",
    "    ts_data = ts_data.asfreq('D', fill_value=0)  # Fill missing days with 0\n",
    "    \n",
    "    print(f\"Time series prepared: {len(ts_data)} days\")\n",
    "    print(f\"Date range: {ts_data.index.min()} to {ts_data.index.max()}\")\n",
    "    print(f\"\\nFirst few rows:\")\n",
    "    print(ts_data.head())"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": {"cell_type": \"markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Cell 3: Stationarity Test"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": {"cell_type": \"code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "try:\n",
    "    from statsmodels.tsa.stattools import adfuller\n",
    "    \n",
    "    result = adfuller(ts_data['incidents'].dropna())\n",
    "    print(\"ADF Test Results:\")\n",
    "    print(f\"  Test Statistic: {result[0]:.4f}\")\n",
    "    print(f\"  P-value: {result[1]:.4f}\")\n",
    "    \n",
    "    if result[1] < 0.05:\n",
    "        print(\"  Result: Series is STATIONARY\")\n",
    "    else:\n",
    "        print(\"  Result: Series is NON-STATIONARY (differencing may be needed)\")\nexcept ImportError:\n",
    "    print(\"âš  statsmodels not installed. Install with: pip install statsmodels\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": {"cell_type": \"markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Cell 4: Visualization"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": {"cell_type": \"code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(14, 6))\n",
    "ts_data['incidents'].plot(ax=ax, label='Daily Incidents')\n",
    "ax.set_title('Daily Crime Incidents Time Series', fontsize=14, fontweight='bold')\n",
    "ax.set_xlabel('Date')\n",
    "ax.set_ylabel('Incidents')\n",
    "ax.legend()\n",
    "plt.tight_layout()\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
  },
  {
